The data contents include: Table 4 electron microprobe data of pyrite and chalcopyrite in baoshandao and Fenghuangshan deposits; Table 5 LA-ICP-MS trace element data of pyrite in baoshandao and Fenghuangshan deposits; Table 6 LA-ICP-MS trace element data of chalcopyrite in Fenghuangshan deposit;
The element composition of pyrite and chalcopyrite was measured by jeol-jxa-8230m electron probe of School of resources and environmental engineering, Hefei University of technology. A total of 50 analysis points were analyzed. The analysis conditions were as follows: accelerating voltage 15kV, probe current 20na, peak diameter 5nm μ m。 The trace element compositions of pyrite and chalcopyrite single crystals were determined by resonance 193nm ArF excimer laser and Agilent 7500a ICP-MS in the State Key Laboratory of isotope geochemistry, Guangzhou Institute of geochemistry, Chinese Academy of Sciences. A total of 150 spots were analyzed.
The above data have been published in SCI high-level journals, and the data are true and reliable. The data is stored in Excel.
